    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Refers to the culture, style, and period associated with the reign of the emperor Chia Ch'ing, 1796-1820. The style is characterized by wares such as snuff bottles, figures, and bottles in varying styles featuring painted blue and copper-red designs, enameling of all kinds, and monochrome glazes.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
